begin_memory_text: We introduced ourselves and talked about where we lived. She told me about the different states she lived in and we talked about weather.
middle_memory_text: We talked about our life, how Covid impacted things, what we do for a living. We briefly discussed our living situations and how it has changed because of Covid
end_memory_text: We talked about our hobbies. We both love Brooklynn 99, she enjoys hiking, rock climbing, arts and crafts. We also talked a bit about kids and how silly they are
rest_of_day_open: Quite stressful. I have a lot of school work that needs to get done, and it often feels like I don't have enough time to do it. I also often feel like a need to unwind but feel guilty for taking a break when I have work to do. Although I am quite excited to catch up with a few of my friends tomorrow
critical_positive: I think we were able to find things to talk about, though it was quite slow. I found my partner easy to talk to and quite engaging as she often asked me questions and wanted to know more. It also felt like the conversation wasn't one sided, she gave me room to talk and she had time to talk as well.
critical_negative: I found it hard to be engaged. Maybe it's because I knew that I was most likely never going to see her again, but I often felt like I couldn't think of things to say or ask. I also couldn't really relate to her much and didn't really know what to say. Mostly when I talk to friends, I ask rather personal questions, but I didn't want to cross any boundaries here.

begin_memory_text: We introduced ourselves, talked about what we had been doing that day, where we lived and the current conditions of the places where we lived.
middle_memory_text: We talked about our jobs, what she was studying in school, past jobs we've had, friends, how covid has affected our lives
end_memory_text: We talked about what we like to watch on tv, more about her school and work, what's keeping her busy currently. she mentioned helping her mom with caring for kids, then we talked about babysitting/how funny kids are
rest_of_day_open: I see the rest of my week going pretty well. It's currently the weekend, the rest of today I'm going to have dinner with a friend then watch a movie likely. Tomorrow I have a virtual modeling session in the morning then might buy some flowers. Monday I'll go back to work but I have a good job so work is pretty easy and pleasant most days!
critical_positive: I think it worked well that we're both female so we felt comfortable with each other. We both are quite agreeable too and were asking questions about interests/ hobbies of the other. There were a few awkward pauses but they were slight and didn't last very long. We didn't have much in common but were open to listening.
critical_negative: I feel like the age difference between us meant that we're in really different places in life and our location within the US has different cultures. I told her a little about utah culture but it's hard to get across. There were a few pauses or a few moments that I felt like I was rambling on too long.
